name: SynPAT_Synthetic_Physical_Theories_Data
description: This dataset contains systems of dimensionally consistent equations generated across different configurations of variable count, derivative count, and equation count. Each configuration includes three generated systems with associated replacements, system data, noisy variants, and consequences. The dataset is designed to benchmark symbolic regression models on machine-assisted physical discovery tasks.
citation: Srivastava et al., SynPAT: A System for Generating Synthetic Physical Theories with Data, NeurIPS 2025 (submitted)

variables.name: num_variables
variables.description: Number of variables in the generated system

variables.name: num_equations
variables.description: Number of equations in each system

variables.name: noise_level
variables.description: Standard deviation of Gaussian noise added to the system or consequence data
